etymology.interpretation: The character 高(gāo, "high; tall") visually represents a tall structure or building, symbolizing height or elevation. Unlike 京(jīng, "capital"), it is straightforwardly a representation of height.

examples.chinese: 那棵树长得高(那棵樹長得高)，比其他树高很多(比其他樹高很多)。
examples.pinyin: Nà kē shù zhǎng de gāo, bǐ qítā shù gāo hěn duō.
examples.english: That tree grows tall, much taller than the other trees.

examples.chinese: 飞机在高空飞行(飛機在高空飛行)。
examples.english: The airplane flies in high altitude.
